race.comment: THREE TEES (8) resumed at Mackay and didn't have the best of it after attempting to buck at the start. He's won a Yeppoon trial since meeting stewards' requirements. He will be sharper today and with the 3kg claimer aboard will be tough to beat. OFFICE POLITICS (5) came off a long break, placing at Thangool as favourite. He's sure to be improved and should manage the longer sprint. Has the tongue tie on again. BOOM CRUSHER (1) resumes and has the blinkers on again. He's had plenty of chances but has run some nice races and jumped favourite here last time. Will likely find this too short but can be running into it. Ditto GREEN CHAI (2), who has switched from the Munce yard on a 54-day return. He's also better over further but maps well and the 2kg claim is handy.
